body_html:
It is not in our support matrix, but grpc makes even contributed support impossible.
IBM has been maintaining support for us.

On the upstream feature request side, boringSSL owners reported that they will not support big endian systems. Therefore our option now is to enable building TF without SSL.

body:
It is not in our support matrix, but grpc makes even contributed support impossible.
IBM has been maintaining support for us.

On the upstream feature request side, boringSSL owners reported that they will not support big endian systems. Therefore our option now is to enable building TF without SSL.
